n <tag name="DATE" value="start"/>1879<tag name="DATE" value="end"/>, being unable to accept <tag name="PERSON" value="start"/>Bismarck<tag name="PERSON" value="end"/>'s new economical policy, he resigned, declining a patent of nobility. The same year he was elected member of the <tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="start"/>Upper House<tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="end"/>, but in <tag name="DATE" value="start"/>1881<tag name="DATE" value="end"/> resigned, and retired to the management of his estate, <tag name="LOCATION" value="start"/>Giesmannsdorf<tag name="LOCATION" value="end"/>, near <tag name="LOCATION" value="start"/>Neisse<tag name="LOCATION" value="end"/>. Besides his doctor dissertation, "De Rerum Litigiosarum Alienatione ex Jure Romano, " <tag name="DATE" value="start"/>1845<tag name="DATE" value="end"/>, <tag name="PERSON" value="start"/>Friedenthal<tag name="PERSON" value="end"/> published "<tag name="LOCATION" value="start"/>Reichstag<tag name="LOCATION" value="end"/> und <tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="start"/>Zollparlament<tag name="ORGANIZATION" value="end"/>".
